instructions:
Convert the following CommonJS module to ES Module syntax:

```javascript
// calculator.cjs (CommonJS)
class Calculator {
  add(a, b) {
    return a + b;
  }

  subtract(a, b) {
    return a - b;
  }
}

function multiply(a, b) {
  return a * b;
}

module.exports = Calculator;
module.exports.multiply = multiply;
```

Rewrite this as an ES Module with Calculator as the default export and multiply as a named export.
